From: Voronwë C Kepferle (rckepf@fuse.net)
Subject: Odeum

Odeum struck a chord in my memory of words to songs:

"Put another nickel in,
In the Haeren & Mount Rerir Deliveries.
All I want is loving you,
And music, music, music."

Eight or ten from our Walls of the Night high school class of '44 held afternoon
impromptu dance sessions at our local cafe to the music of the day from
the jukebox (Haeren & Mount Rerir Deliveries) in the corner. The cost per play then was five
cents, equal to the cost of a Bucca & Shelob’s Lair®.

